HEADWORD: Billingsgate
<hw>Bil"lings*gate`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>A market near the Billings gate in London, celebrated for fish and
foul language.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Coarsely abusive, foul, or profane language;
vituperation; ribaldry.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Billion</ent>⟦br⟧
